<br>
5. What is one piece of advice for a new Cleric?<br>
<br>
      Know your limits.  Clericing, from my limited experience, is quite different from group to group.  Sometimes you can take a beating, sometimes you are just a healer.  We are the worst travellers of any casting class; no invis/camouflage, levitate, enduring breath, or speed enhancement.  We can be the biggest asset to a party, or its biggest detriment, depending on our ability to time heals and save mana efficiently.  The ability to not panic, and to cast Divine Aura/Barrier when needed is also, I think, vital.<br>
<br>
Above all, I guess, is a willingness to die, and to accept the cruel fact that you cannot save everyone, and hopefully everyone you group with will understand this.  I tend to find very good groups on this server, since we are the best one <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  , and if I have to get a little bossy and stop somebody from pulling, they listen.<br>
<br>
I think clerics are a very hard class to play, but very rewarding.  Leastways I feel all fuzzy when my group survives somethin they probably wouldn't have without my presence.<br>
