2. What level are you? 52 <br>
3. What deity do you follow? Innoruuk<br>
4. What alignment are you on FV? Order Evil<br>
5. What is one piece of advice for a new Cleric?<br>
Max your defence skill, specialize in alteration, don't nuke unless you are over 80m and your buffs are current, if you're in a dungeon symbol everyone, have a hotkey to target your chanter, keep your stun (the one without damage) memed to help your chanter, get used to figuring out who is expendable,  Worship Innoruuk and get a clickable snare not the best thing out there but it's better than none. Learn to group, and what your spells do in the group, and take some time to solo.<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dalninil>Dalninil</A> at: 4/22/02 10:26:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubraxom.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Braxom</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/31/02 11:15:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: mm...</span><hr size=1> Level- 39<br>
Race- Dorf<br>
Deity- Brell<br>
Alignment- Nuetral/Nuetral<br>
<br>
Advice- 1. Keep defence maxed so you can take some hits, this will make it easier for your other group members to pull mobs off you instead of having to chase you around as you run for your life.<br>
Advice- 2. Keep everyone informed as to what you are doing, make a hotkey that announces your heals and give frequent mana reports. <br>
Advice- 3. Know the Hp of the people you are healing and choose the right heal for the job, do not get it stuck in your head that you will just use superior or complete healing on everyone, this will cause overheals and waste alot of mana.<br>
Advice- 3. Learn languages, by speaking the different languages of norath you will open up doors to many more grouping possibilities, being a cleric is not much fun if you cant find a group<br>
Advice-4 Help everyone you can, a little bit of time on your part can pay off big in the future, you will need the help of other classes later on to do quests and such.<br>
advice- 5 Choose a name that is original but simple, the easier your name is to remember the better chance you have of being sent a tell by someone looking for a group.<br>
<br>
-Braxom<br>
