<br>
2. What level are you? - 34<br>
<br>
3. What deity do you follow? - Tunare<br>
<br>
4. What alignment are you on FV? - Order Good, I think<br>
<br>
5. What is one piece of advice for a new Cleric? - Spells, spells, spells. Read up on all your spells ahead of time, and be sure to buy and use them! Very few of our spells are truly useless, and it's easy to overlook some important things. Examples: Our stun line of spells, to stop enemy casters from casting and a quick way to stop runners; The summoned-hammer line of spells, nice low level magic weapon and always fun vs. undead; Divine Aura line - may seem like a waste of  a spell slot with it's ten-minute recycle, but trust me, you will come to rely on this spell. Keep your Resistance and Cure spells up to date, grab those utility spells like Cancel Magic and Invigor. Many clerics seem to think all they can do is heal, nuke, and HP buff, and that just isn't so. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uyugisha.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yugisha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/5/02 10:52:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> 1. What race are you? &lt;b&gt;halfling&lt;/b&gt;<br>
