5. Have a good Meat shield to keep things off you and everyone else  *giggle at Veloxia*... :P  Seriously though I learned to be a good cleric by being a Druid for 56 seasons on Quellious (in my opinion you need to be a really good healer as a Druid in a group situation, even better than a cleric since your heals are so limited).  You have to learn the limits of your heals, not only time wise in casting but how much they heal on certain classes.  Know your Group, know thier roles and what they are doing to bennifit the group.  Certain actions cause a lot of aggro and need to watch the health of those doing those actions with a close eye.  (i.e. enchanters need to be watched at all times, they drop so quickly).  Oh and get your Heal over time spells (Luclin and Velious ones)... those spells are too cool.<br>
